      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRECIOUS GOD (2) stuck on fairly from a midfield position over further last time out, finishing 1.5L off the winner. Nottle now hops on board with a return to the mile looking ideal. Can land in a midfield position today and can get back to winning ways. I'M NIPOTE (1) got well back over 1400m at this track last time out before flashing home to just miss. Out to 1600m now is a big tick and he boasts a strong third-up record. Can play a leading role from an inside barrier. AURORA QUEEN (3) went back-to-back last start when scoring by 0.8L over this trip at Albany. CJP rides from a good draw and while this is tougher, she looks to have hit her straps. Draw is tricky but she looks to be trending the right way now. TRIBAL RULER (6) can bounce back in what looks a suitable race for him. HE'S ARCHIE (5) is next best.",
